# Breaking Free Connect - Frontend Mock-up

This is a small frontend mock-up built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

## What the mock-up does

- Simulates a Polygon wallet connection
- Generates a mock wallet address
- Lets a user register with an email, display name, and password
- Checks that the password is at least 8 characters
- Checks that both password fields match
- Saves mock user data using browser local storage
- Shows a setup confirmation page
- Displays a simple dashboard
- Tracks a daily message quota
- Lets users send mock messages to a recipient ID
- Shows recent message activity

## Current project stage

This is only a frontend prototype. It does not currently use a real backend, database, email verification system, or real Web3 wallet connection.

## End goal

The final version would include a backend and database so users can securely register, log in, verify their email, connect a real Polygon wallet, and send approved messages to team members using their User ID without exposing private email addresses.

## Built with

- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript
- Local Storage